The paper focuses on evaluating the interpretability and utility of machine learning models in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the ethical and responsible application of machine learning, which is a common theme in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The study involves human-computer interaction and user performance, which is relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for evaluating the effectiveness of interpretation, which is related to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses design guidance for natural language processing human-in-the-loop settings, which is relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
